Name: fileutil
Synopsis: Helpers for working with files and filesystems

Variables.Name: DirExists
Variables.Comment: Alias functions from pathutil as a convenience

Variables.Name: SkipToken
Variables.Comment:
By default, the underlying bufio.Scanner that tokenizes the input data
will discard the tokens that it's splitting on.  however, in most cases, we
don't actually want this.  however, if the thing we're removing IS this token,
then we will have removed the token, then immediately put it back in the stream.

Returning the SkipToken error will tell the ReadManipulator to not put this token
back into the stream, but otherwise not produce an actual error during read.

Functions.Name: CompareReaders
Functions.Comment:
Compare the binary contents of two io.Reader instances.  The result will be 0 if a==b, -1 if a < b, and +1 if a > b.
An optional hash.Hash instance may be given, otherwise the default crypto/sha256 will be used.
Functions.Signature: CompareReaders(a io.Reader, b io.Reader, hasher ...hash.Hash) int

Functions.Name: CopyDir
Functions.Comment:
Recursively walk the entries of a given directory, calling CopyEntryFunc for each entry.
The io.Writer returned from the function will have that file's contents written to it.  If
the io.Writer is nil, the file will not be written anywhere but no error will be returned.
If CopyEntryFunc returns an error, the behavior will be consistent with filepath.WalkFunc

Functions.Name: CopyFile
Functions.Comment:
Copy a file from one place to another.  Source can be an io.Reader or string.  If source is a
string, the string will be passed to the Open() function as a URL.  Destination can be an
io.Writer or string.  If destination is a string, it will be treated as a local filesystem path
to write the data read from source to.

If either source or destination implements io.Closer, thee files will be closed before this
function returns.

Functions.Name: GetMimeType
Functions.Comment:
GetMimeType goes out of its way to really, really try to figure out the MIME type of a given
filename or io.Reader.  If the first argument satisfies the io.Seeker interface, the seeker
will Seek() back to the beginning.  If it satisfies the io.Closer interface, it will be closed.

Functions.Name: GetNthLine
Functions.Comment: Attempt to return the nth line (starting from 1) in the given file or reader.

Functions.Name: IsModifiedAfter
Functions.Comment: Return true if the given FileInfo sports a ModTime later than the current file.

Functions.Name: ManipulateAll
Functions.Comment:
Performs multiple sequential manipulations on an intercepted line of text from
an io.Reader as its being read.

Functions.Name: MustGetNthLine
Functions.Comment: A panicky version of GetNthLine.

Functions.Name: MustReadAllLines
Functions.Comment: A panicky version of ReadAllLines.

Functions.Name: MustWriteFile
Functions.Comment: Same as WriteFile, but will panic if the file cannot be written.

Functions.Name: MustWriteTempFile
Functions.Comment:
Same as MustWriteFile, but writes the given input to a temporary file, returning
the filename.  The function will panic if the file cannot be written.

Functions.Name: Open
Functions.Comment: Calls OpenWithOptions with no options set.

Functions.Name: OpenWithOptions
Functions.Comment:
A generic URL opener that supports various schemes and returns an io.Reader.
Supported URL schemes include: file://, http://, https://, ftp://, sftp://. If no scheme is
provided, the URL is interpreted as a local filesystem path.

Functions.Name: ReadAll
Functions.Comment:
Takes the given string filename, []byte, io.Reader, or io.ReadCloser and returns
the bytes therein.

Functions.Name: ReadAllLines
Functions.Comment: Read all lines of text from the given file and return them as a slice.

Functions.Name: ReadAllString
Functions.Comment: A string version of ReadAll.

Functions.Name: RegisterOpenHandler
Functions.Comment: Register a handler for a new or existing URL scheme, for use with Open() and OpenWithOptions()

Functions.Name: RemoveBlankLines
Functions.Comment: A ReadManipulatorFunc for removing lines that only contain whitespace.

Functions.Name: RemoveLinesContaining
Functions.Comment: A ReadManipulatorFunc for removing lines that contain the given string.

Functions.Name: RemoveLinesSurroundedBy
Functions.Comment: A ReadManipulatorFunc for removing lines surrounded by a given prefix and suffix.
Functions.Signature: RemoveLinesSurroundedBy(prefix string, suffix string, trimSpace bool) ReadManipulatorFunc

Functions.Name: RemoveLinesWithPrefix
Functions.Comment: A ReadManipulatorFunc for removing lines that have a given prefix.

Functions.Name: RemoveLinesWithSuffix
Functions.Comment: A ReadManipulatorFunc for removing lines that have a given suffix.

Functions.Name: RemoveOpenHandler
Functions.Comment: Removes a registered URL scheme handler.

Functions.Name: ReplaceWith
Functions.Comment: A ReadManipulatorFunc for replacing text in an io.Reader as its being read.
Functions.Signature: ReplaceWith(find string, replace string, occurrences int) ReadManipulatorFunc

Functions.Name: SameFile
Functions.Comment:
Returns whether two files represent the same file.  If a string is given for either file, os.Stat will be run on that
path.  If os.FileInfo is given for either file, it will be passed to os.SameFile directly.  If either file is an
io.Reader, the contents of both files will be read and hashed using CompareHasher.  If the hashes are identical, the
files are considered the same.  Any error encountered and this function will return false.

Functions.Name: SetExt
Functions.Comment:
Detects the file extension of the given path and replaces it with the given extension.  The optional
second argument allows you to explictly specify the extension (if known).
Functions.Signature: SetExt(path string, ext string, oldexts ...string) string

Functions.Name: ShouldGetNthLine
Functions.Comment: Attempts to call GetNthLine, but will return an empty string if there is an error.  Does not panic.

Functions.Name: ShouldReadAllLines
Functions.Comment: Attempts to call ReadAllLines, but will return an empty slice if there is an error.  Does not panic.

Functions.Name: SizeOf
Functions.Comment: Returns the size of the given filename, or zero if any error is encountered (or if the file is zero length).

Functions.Name: WriteFile
Functions.Comment:
Write the contents of the given io.Reader, []byte, or string to the specified filename.
Filename paths containing tilde (~) will automatically expand to the current
user's home directory, and all intermediate parent directories will be automatically
created.  Will return the number of bytes written, or an error.

Functions.Name: WriteTempFile
Functions.Comment:
Same as WriteFile, but writes the given input to a temporary file, returning
the filename.

DirReader.Name: DirReader

Methods.Name: Close
Methods.Comment: close open files and reset the internal reader

Methods.Name: SetSkipFunc
Methods.Comment:
Set a function that will be called for each path encountered while reading.
If this function returns true, that path (and its descedants) will not be read.

DirReader.Comment:
A DirReader provides a streaming io.Reader interface to all files in a given
directory, with options for handling unreadable entries and recursion.

FileInfo.Name: FileInfo
FileInfo.Comment: An os.FileInfo-compatible wrapper that allows for individual values to be overridden.

Methods.Name: NewPostReadCloser
Methods.Comment:
Implements an io.ReadCloser that can be configured to perform cleanup options whenever the
Close() function is called.
